'''Old Galactic Standard''' was a combination of [[Alien/Legends|alien]] ([[Durese/Legends|Durese]] and [[Bothese]]) and [[Notron Cant|early]] [[Human/Legends|Human]] languages meshed together.

The language was in use even before the [[Tionese War]].<ref name="Written Word" />

It was a pidgin of traders and [[Spacer/Legends|spacers]]. That way, it spread throughout [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] and others, non-spacers, also learned it in order to be able to communicate with other species; eventually it was adopted officially as the language of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] and the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].

It was the precursor of [[Mid-Galactic Standard]] and [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Galactic Basic Standard]], and was still in use as of the [[Pius Dea Era]]. [[Arden Lyn]] was a speaker of this language. By the time of the [[Dark Wars]], Jedi Master [[Atris]] could still speak it.

